Ask HN: How much effort it takes to build decent video/interactive explainers?
text: I am referring math videos by 3b1b made with manim, blogs with interactive explorables etc. 3b1b makes stunning content but at a slow pace of two months or so per video. What is slowing them? Is it due to difficulty to create prototype because of clunky tools, or slow hardware that drags REPL behind? In addition to the abundance of programming languages and animation tools, What software or medium can we create to make this process more efficient?
